To create a simple HTML website that displays a random joke from a list of four jokes when a button is clicked, you can use HTML for the structure, CSS for basic styling, and JavaScript for the interactive functionality. Below is an example of how you can implement this:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Random Joke Generator</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 50px;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            font-size: 16px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Random Joke Generator</h1>
    <button onclick="showRandomJoke()">Tell me a joke</button>
    <p id="jokeDisplayArea"></p>

    <script>
        // List of jokes
        const jokes = [
            "What do you call fake spaghetti? An impasta.",
            "Why don’t skeletons fight each other? They don’t have the guts.",
            "Why couldn't the bicycle stand up by itself? It was two tired!",
            "What do you get when you cross a snowman with a vampire? Frostbite."
        ];

        function showRandomJoke() {
            // Get a random joke index
            const randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * jokes.length);
            // Select the joke
            const joke = jokes[randomIndex];
            // Display the joke in the paragraph with id="jokeDisplayArea"
            document.getElementById('jokeDisplayArea').innerText = joke;
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:

1. **HTML Structure**: The HTML structure consists of a heading (`<h1>`), a button, and a paragraph (`<p>`) where the joke will be displayed.

2. **CSS Styling**: The styling is minimal, just to make the text centrally aligned and to style the button a bit.

3. **JavaScript**: The JavaScript part is where the functionality lies:
   - An array `jokes` contains the four jokes.
   - The function `showRandomJoke()` is executed when the button is clicked (`onclick="showRandomJoke()"`):
     - It selects a random joke from the array using `Math.random()` and displays it in the paragraph with the ID `jokeDisplayArea`.

This simple website will display a random joke from the predefined list every time the user clicks the button.

